==Reception==
''The Grim Adventures of Billy & Mandy'' received critical acclaim and became one of Cartoon Network's top rated and most popular series. [[Common Sense Media]] gave the show a 3/5 star rating and stated that it has "goofy punchlines and obscure cultural references", and recommends the viewer age be at least 8 years old.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.commonsensemedia.org/tv-reviews/grim-adventures-billy-and-mandy|title=The Grim Adventures of Billy and Mandy|work=[[Common Sense Media]]|accessdate=May 28, 2012}}</ref> The series has won one [[Annie Award]], two [[Emmy Awards]] and including those three wins, has been nominated a total of nine times for various awards. New episodes were broadcast on Cartoon Network Fridays at 7:30pm to over 1 million viewers an episode.

